two new non-executive directors as soon as next month, the
Sunday Telegraph newspaper reported, without citing anyone.  The appointments are in the final stages of approval with
the Financial Services Authority, the Telegraph said.  Lloyds Chairman Win Bischoff, who turns 71 next year, may
announce his retirement at the companyâ€™s 2013 annual meeting,
the newspaper reported.  Nicole Sharp, a Lloyds spokeswoman in  London , declined to
